history.content: Starting in Fall 2016, the new Student Information Systems at the campus level will block students from signing up for any conflicting classes.  It's still technically possible for Spring 16, and we understand that in cases where the university has been unable to avoid conflicting lecture times for classes you want to take simultaneously this might sometimes make sense if one of the lectures is webcast and there are no final exam conflicts.  That being said, of course useful information is shared during lecture -- including just being able to check-in with other students in the class immediately after lecture -- and we'd encourage you to avoid creating a conflict with your lecture only to be able to choose a more convenient lab time for another class.

children.subject: Whoa, I never thought Telebears would be replaced during my lifetime.
